<br>
Your local body shop is one of the best places to get affordable cars, you can save a good deal of money by buying a rebuilt with a salvage title.  it's instpected before it's retitled and I've found them to be in very good condition in general, jsut make sure you go to a reputable shop.  <br>
<br>
I would suggest you take your 2k and borrow 2k more and get something decent, like let's say a rebuilt 98ish maybe 99 grand am with low mileage if you can find it. or if you don't mind financing a little more and you live in the detroit area check out autorex in waterford, talk to dave. <br>
<br>
but if you must stay with 2k I'd suggest an import, as they generally are more reliable, run longer than domestics and are usually cheaper.  <br>
<br>
I would also suggest you take the vehicle to a shop such as any firestone store and have it inspected this will run you anywhere fom 9.99 to 19.99 and you get a good thorough inspection.  Or you can go to a place with free inspections such a tuffy but it's usually a crappy inspection since the tech doesn't get paid for doing it in most of those deals.<br>
