 management end up getting dicked in the end, wich is great because the reps end up making a fat wad for their pocket without feeling the slightest bit guilty. If you spread your visits out with them (don't buy the first time), and find a rep that you have something in common with to talk about, They will eventually want to help you out. Now this is key... make sure the day you are going to buy is a slow day (usually a tuesday or wednesday) come in about 11am or so. They will have been open a few hours and anxious for a sale. Figure out something you can handle, 2k down maybe with 150 a month payment... something like that. Whatever it is your comfortable with stick to it. Make sure its your day off cause you could spend anywhere from 2-6+ hours there, but eventually they will take your deal. Make sure you are very nice because they will want to take care of you. People always think that salesmen are trying to pressure them and that they are assholes so in turn they should be assholes back but not the case at all. The more of a dick you are the more you get dicked. Dealerships pay rock bottom prices for used vehicles and if your patient enough you too can get them for rock bottom prices. My car I bought from a dealership using pretty much the same method I just described. sticker price was 8k at the time. after many many visits and talking with the same person and management I learned that they only paid 2.5k for it and while they can't let it go for 0 profit they can let it go for 500 over what they paid bare minimum. I bought an 8k stickered car for 3.5k (I could have got it for 3k but I wanted my rep to get some money from the deal). to rap it up, the car has run solid with no fixes besides regular maintenance. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.discreetww.com/snuff.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.